            <fr:title text="Forester 4.1 › new forester init command"><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-00S9.xml" title="Forester 4.1" addr="//forester/jms-00S9" type="local">Forester 4.1</fr:link> › new <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>To make it easier to set up a new forest, we have added a <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command; when you run this command in an empty directory, it will initialise a git repository with a submodule for the <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme" type="external">default theme</fr:link> pinned to the correct release, and a <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-00RG.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › forest configuration via TOML" addr="//forester/jms-00RG" type="local">configuration file</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
